{"actual_usd":0.158845,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":371,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30656,"reply":"\"Well, those are the two natural roads people usually try first.\" *I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, as if lining the thoughts up before I set them down.* \"Either the witnesses were mistaken because grief can do strange things, or else Jesus never fully died and the whole thing only looked like resurrection.\"\n\n\"The trouble is, neither explanation really bears the full weight of what the accounts are trying to carry.\" *I lean back a little, my white tie catching the morning light.* \"Grief visions might account for one or two private experiences, maybe. They do a poor job with the stubborn public shape of the testimony — meals, conversations, repeated appearances, frightened men becoming bold men, and a movement built not on 'we felt him with us' but 'God raised him from the dead.' And the 'didn't really die' road has its own problem: a half-dead man staggering out of a tomb does not create resurrection faith. He creates a medical emergency.\"\n\n\"So why insist on the supernatural?\" *I lift one shoulder.* \"Because the claim itself is supernatural. Christianity isn't mainly saying, 'Something meaningful happened in the disciples' hearts.' It's saying God acted in history. If you shave that down to what modern people find manageable, you've kept some religious feeling, but you've lost the actual Christian claim.\"\n\n\"Now—\" *I tap the page once, gently.* \"That doesn't mean you stop asking hard questions. It just means the question becomes: which explanation best fits the total picture? And for me, the resurrection is one of those places where the natural explanations start looking thinner than the miracle they're trying to avoid. Which part of it catches in your throat most — the visions idea, or the question of whether dead people stay dead?\"","rolling_24h_usd":69.97563999999998,"run_id":"a3ee3d0a-2a77-4ce7-b131-0958a2fcf3e9"}
